Full Size ImageClick to close full size. Item Description 2005 Fender Custom Shop Custom Classic Stratocaster V-Neck Electric Guitar in very good condition with little to no playwear. There are a couple of ultra-fine scratches that cannot be seen by the camera. Classic 3-tone Sunburst finish with 3-ply white parchment pickguard and chrome hardware. The guitar has a nice action and the figured birds-eye one-piece maple neck with a "V" profile has a very good, quality feel. The medium jumbo frets are in excellent condition. The Modern Classic pickups and the Hot Classic bridge pickup with an induction plate have great tone with nice output. The No-Load tone circuit lets the sound of the pickups shine. The guitar features a two point tremolo with polished stainless saddles and staggered height locking tuners for great tuning stability. There is a Fender Custom Shop Logo on the back of the headstock and on the neck plate. Another great quality instrument from the Fender Custom Shop with lots of great player features. Includes a nice tweed hard shell case and a replacement tremolo arm. Serial Number: CZ506620 Weight: 7 lbs. 14 oz.The American Strat Goes Upscale with the Custom ClassicThe magic of the Fender Custom Shop is in the hands of the builders! Their years of experience, range of skills and expertise at their craft make every Fender guitar they build highly sought-after by players, celebrities and collectors. That's the case with the Custom Classic Stratocaster V-Neck! Fender Custom Classic Stratocaster V-Neck at a Glance: An American Strat with custom features Select alder body and "V" maple neck Modern Classic single-coil pickups and Hot Classic bridge pickup The Custom Classic Stratocaster is the Custom Shop's version of Fender's American Series Strat. It offers custom detailing, classic Fender contours and legendary Strat tone. The aged white plastic parts contribute to the Strat's classic looks, and a new deluxe 2-point synchronized tremolo with polished solid stainless steel saddles and block make it fun to play. Select alder body and “V” maple neckThe Fender Custom Classic Stratocaster includes additional upgraded features. It’s built with a thin-finished select alder body. The Strat’s birds-eye figured, soft (slightly rounded) “V”-shaped one-piece maple neck is complemented by 22 medium-jumbo frets, and Fender Deluxe staggered height locking machine heads. The one-piece maple neck/fretboard is what gives the Custom Classic Strat that bright, “poppy” classic Fender attack. The alder body wood brings the classic rock sounds of Jimi Hendrix, Stevie Ray Vaughn, and John Mayer to the table. Modern Classic single-coil pickupsFender has upgraded the Custom Classic Stratocaster pickup section, too. The Strat's three Modern Classic single-coil pickups include the Hot Classic bridge pickup with a custom steel inductance plate. Also onboard this Strat is a 3-ply parchment pickguard and a Custom Classic 2-point synchronized tremolo with milled solid-stainless saddles, solid steel spring block.
